2026-06-24 20:32:33,913 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=69c913e2d188aa3ad684bf70f4406deb span=896c52dbd57b1e5c parent=- | {'role': 'tool', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call_response', 'id': 'fc_9ed787b3-ebbd-4d5f-aee8-36553f1bf1e7', 'response': 'Based on the current pricing policy, the pricing floor for a **BB-rated AED loan** is determined as a minimum spread over the internal Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP) rate (which is published monthly by FAB Treasury). \n\nThe applicable floor depends on the facility structure and tenor:\n\n### 1. Corporate Term Loans\nFor standard term loans, the minimum margin floors are (Source: `FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4` · Section 3.1):\n* **Tenor ≤ 1 Year:** 165 bps over FTP\n* **Tenor 1–3 Years:** 210 bps over FTP\n* **Tenor 3–5 Years:** 260 bps over FTP\n* **Tenor > 5 Years:** 320 bps over FTP\n\n### 2. Revolving Credit Facilities (RCFs)\nFor RCFs, the minimum drawn margin floor is **(Source: `FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4` · Section 3.2):\n* **Drawn Margin Floor:** 160 bps over FTP \n*(Note: An additional 40 bps facility fee floor applies if the tenure exceeds 3 years.)*\n\n### ⚠️ Execution Rules & Adjustments\n* **Calculation:** The minimum all-in rate a Relationship Manager can offer is the **current AED FTP rate + the floor spread above**. \n* **Relationship Value Adjustments:** Under certain documented cross-sell conditions (exceeding AED 500,000 annual revenue), the floor may be reduced by up to **25 bps** with credit authority approval (`FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4` · Section 2.4).\n* **Below-Floor Pricing:** Any pricing below these stated floors is a policy breach unless a formal **Pricing Exception** is documented and approved by the appropriate credit committee (`FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4` · Section 6).\n\nPlease verify the current AED FTP rate on the internal Treasury pricing portal to calculate the final all-in percentage rate for your term sheet.'}]}
2026-06-24 20:32:36,014 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=69c913e2d188aa3ad684bf70f4406deb span=896c52dbd57b1e5c parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'text', 'content': '**Pricing floor for a BB‑rated AED loan (FAB policy)**  \n\n| Facility type | Tenor / Conditions | Minimum spread over the internal AED FTP rate* |\n|---------------|-------------------|----------------------------------------------|\n| **Corporate Term Loans** | ≤\u202f1\u202fyear | **165\u202fbps** |\n|  | 1\u202f–\u202f3\u202fyears | **210\u202fbps** |\n|  | 3\u202f–\u202f5\u202fyears | **260\u202fbps** |\n|  | >\u202f5\u202fyears | **320\u202fbps** |\n| **Revolving Credit Facilities (RCFs)** | Any tenor (drawn margin) | **160\u202fbps** |\n|  | Tenure\u202f>\u202f3\u202fyears (facility‑fee component) | Additional **40\u202fbps** floor |\n\n**Source:** `FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4`, **Section\u202f3.1** (term‑loan floors) and **Section\u202f3.2** (RCF floor).\n\n---\n\n### Additional execution notes  \n\n* The all‑in rate offered to a client is **AED\u202fFTP\u202f+\u202ffloor spread** (as above).  \n* **Relationship‑value adjustment:** For relationships with ≥\u202fAED\u202f500,000 annual revenue, the floor may be reduced by up to **25\u202fbps** with credit‑authority approval (Section\u202f2.4).  \n* **Below‑floor pricing:** Any rate below these floors is a policy breach unless a formal **Pricing Exception** is documented and approved by the appropriate credit committee (Section\u202f6).  \n\n*Please confirm the current AED FTP rate on the internal Treasury pricing portal to calculate the final all‑in percentage.*  '}]}
2026-06-24 20:32:36,014 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=69c913e2d188aa3ad684bf70f4406deb span=258e544714a24886 parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call', 'id': 'fc_9ed787b3-ebbd-4d5f-aee8-36553f1bf1e7', 'name': 'query_knowledge_base', 'arguments': '{"question":"What is the pricing floor for a BB-rated AED loan?"}'}]}
2026-06-24 20:32:36,015 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=69c913e2d188aa3ad684bf70f4406deb span=258e544714a24886 parent=- | {'role': 'tool', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call_response', 'id': 'fc_9ed787b3-ebbd-4d5f-aee8-36553f1bf1e7', 'response': 'Based on the current pricing policy, the pricing floor for a **BB-rated AED loan** is determined as a minimum spread over the internal Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP) rate (which is published monthly by FAB Treasury). \n\nThe applicable floor depends on the facility structure and tenor:\n\n### 1. Corporate Term Loans\nFor standard term loans, the minimum margin floors are (Source: `FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4` · Section 3.1):\n* **Tenor ≤ 1 Year:** 165 bps over FTP\n* **Tenor 1–3 Years:** 210 bps over FTP\n* **Tenor 3–5 Years:** 260 bps over FTP\n* **Tenor > 5 Years:** 320 bps over FTP\n\n### 2. Revolving Credit Facilities (RCFs)\nFor RCFs, the minimum drawn margin floor is **(Source: `FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4` · Section 3.2):\n* **Drawn Margin Floor:** 160 bps over FTP \n*(Note: An additional 40 bps facility fee floor applies if the tenure exceeds 3 years.)*\n\n### ⚠️ Execution Rules & Adjustments\n* **Calculation:** The minimum all-in rate a Relationship Manager can offer is the **current AED FTP rate + the floor spread above**. \n* **Relationship Value Adjustments:** Under certain documented cross-sell conditions (exceeding AED 500,000 annual revenue), the floor may be reduced by up to **25 bps** with credit authority approval (`FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4` · Section 2.4).\n* **Below-Floor Pricing:** Any pricing below these stated floors is a policy breach unless a formal **Pricing Exception** is documented and approved by the appropriate credit committee (`FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4` · Section 6).\n\nPlease verify the current AED FTP rate on the internal Treasury pricing portal to calculate the final all-in percentage rate for your term sheet.'}]}
2026-06-24 20:32:36,015 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=69c913e2d188aa3ad684bf70f4406deb span=258e544714a24886 parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'text', 'content': '**Pricing floor for a BB‑rated AED loan (FAB policy)**  \n\n| Facility type | Tenor / Conditions | Minimum spread over the internal AED FTP rate* |\n|---------------|-------------------|----------------------------------------------|\n| **Corporate Term Loans** | ≤\u202f1\u202fyear | **165\u202fbps** |\n|  | 1\u202f–\u202f3\u202fyears | **210\u202fbps** |\n|  | 3\u202f–\u202f5\u202fyears | **260\u202fbps** |\n|  | >\u202f5\u202fyears | **320\u202fbps** |\n| **Revolving Credit Facilities (RCFs)** | Any tenor (drawn margin) | **160\u202fbps** |\n|  | Tenure\u202f>\u202f3\u202fyears (facility‑fee component) | Additional **40\u202fbps** floor |\n\n**Source:** `FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4`, **Section\u202f3.1** (term‑loan floors) and **Section\u202f3.2** (RCF floor).\n\n---\n\n### Additional execution notes  \n\n* The all‑in rate offered to a client is **AED\u202fFTP\u202f+\u202ffloor spread** (as above).  \n* **Relationship‑value adjustment:** For relationships with ≥\u202fAED\u202f500,000 annual revenue, the floor may be reduced by up to **25\u202fbps** with credit‑authority approval (Section\u202f2.4).  \n* **Below‑floor pricing:** Any rate below these floors is a policy breach unless a formal **Pricing Exception** is documented and approved by the appropriate credit committee (Section\u202f6).  \n\n*Please confirm the current AED FTP rate on the internal Treasury pricing portal to calculate the final all‑in percentage.*  '}]}
