2026-06-24 20:41:09,214 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=c8ec77786a7b45bdac3ec0f6face0ee7 span=829e524a09fbb7be parent=- | {'role': 'tool', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call_response', 'id': 'fc_5250d859-ab16-4685-8406-3f6ccee18426', 'response': 'Based on the FAB Credit Pricing Policy, the pricing floor for a **BB-rated corporate term loan** is determined as a **spread over the internal Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP) rate**, and varies by facility tenor:\n\n| Facility Tenor | Minimum Pricing Floor (Spread over FTP) |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **≤ 1 Year** | 165 bps |\n| **1 – 3 Years** | 210 bps |\n| **3 – 5 Years** | 260 bps |\n| **> 5 Years** | 320 bps |\n\n*Source: `FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4`, Section 3.1 (Table 3.1)*\n\n**Important Policy Notes:**\n* **FTP Base:** These floors represent risk-based margins. The final all-in minimum rate is calculated as `Current FTP Rate + Applicable Floor Spread`. Actual FTP rates are published monthly by Treasury.\n* **Relationship Value Discount:** The standard floor may be reduced by up to **25 bps** if the client demonstrates material cross-sell contributions (documented annual revenue > AED 500,000 across the FAB relationship), subject to credit authority approval. `[FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · Section 2.4]`\n* **Pricing Exceptions:** Pricing a transaction below the applicable floor for BB-rated clients requires a formal **Pricing Exception** to be documented and approved prior to term sheet issuance. `[FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · Section 6]`\n\n*(Note: If you are pricing a Revolving Credit Facility or Syndicated Loan rather than a standard term loan, the floor structures differ. Let me know if you need those parameters.)*'}]}
2026-06-24 20:41:12,836 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=c8ec77786a7b45bdac3ec0f6face0ee7 span=829e524a09fbb7be parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'text', 'content': '**Pricing Floor for BB‑rated AED Corporate Loans**\n\n| Facility Tenor | Minimum Pricing Floor (Spread over FTP) |\n|---|---|\n| ≤\u202f1\u202fYear | 165\u202fbps |\n| 1\u202f–\u202f3\u202fYears | 210\u202fbps |\n| 3\u202f–\u202f5\u202fYears | 260\u202fbps |\n| >\u202f5\u202fYears | 320\u202fbps |\n\n*Source: **FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4**, Section\u202f3.1 (Table\u202f3.1)*  \n\n**Key Policy Notes**\n\n- **FTP Base:** The floor is added to the current internal Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP) rate. The final all‑in minimum rate = `Current FTP Rate + Applicable Floor Spread`. FTP rates are published monthly by Treasury.  \n\n- **Relationship Value Discount:** The standard floor may be reduced by up to **25\u202fbps** for clients with material cross‑sell contributions (annual revenue\u202f>\u202fAED\u202f500,000 across the FAB relationship), subject to credit authority approval. *Source: FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4, Section\u202f2.4*  \n\n- **Pricing Exceptions:** Any pricing below the applicable floor for BB‑rated clients requires a formal **Pricing Exception** documented and approved before issuing a term sheet. *Source: FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4, Section\u202f6*  \n\n*(If you need the floor structure for revolving credit facilities, syndicated loans, or other product types, please let me know.)*'}]}
