2026-06-25 11:23:48,828 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=a6edd2b1326bf42ed53e597374a43684 span=28f83a4d62a98ee1 parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call', 'id': 'fc_f93f043c-ac1b-4822-9c0a-6cf7db1930bb', 'name': 'query_knowledge_base', 'arguments': '{"question":"pricing floor for a BB-rated AED loan"}'}]}
2026-06-25 11:23:48,828 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=a6edd2b1326bf42ed53e597374a43684 span=28f83a4d62a98ee1 parent=- | {'role': 'tool', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call_response', 'id': 'fc_f93f043c-ac1b-4822-9c0a-6cf7db1930bb', 'response': 'Based on the **FAB Credit Pricing Policy v2.4**, the minimum all-in pricing floors for a **BB-rated AED Corporate Term Loan** are set as the following spreads over the matching AED Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP) rate:\n\n* **Up to 1 Year:** 165 bps over FTP\n* **1–3 Years:** 210 bps over FTP\n* **3–5 Years:** 260 bps over FTP\n* **> 5 Years:** 320 bps over FTP\n\n*(Source: `[FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 3.1]`)*\n\n**Important Notes:**\n* **Relationship Value Adjustments:** If the client demonstrates material cross-sell revenues (exceeding AED 500,000 p.a.), the required margin floor may be reduced by up to 25 bps with appropriate credit authority approval. `([FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 2.4])`\n* **Revolving Credit Facilities (RCFs):** If the facility is an RCF rather than a standard term loan, the BB-rated drawn margin floor is 160 bps over FTP (adding a further 40 bps for tenors >3 years), plus a 40 bps commitment fee floor and a 20 bps facility fee floor. `([FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 3.2])`\n* **Exceptions:** Pricing below these floors requires a formal Pricing Exception (documented RAROC, commercial justification, and executive approvals). `([FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 6.1])`'}]}
2026-06-25 11:23:50,340 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=a6edd2b1326bf42ed53e597374a43684 span=28f83a4d62a98ee1 parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'text', 'content': '**Pricing floor for a BB‑rated AED loan (Corporate Term Loan)**  \n\n- **Up to 1\u202fYear:**\u202f165\u202fbps over AED FTP  \n- **1\u202f–\u202f3\u202fYears:**\u202f210\u202fbps over AED FTP  \n- **3\u202f–\u202f5\u202fYears:**\u202f260\u202fbps over AED FTP  \n- **>\u202f5\u202fYears:**\u202f320\u202fbps over AED FTP  \n\n**Source:** FAB Credit Pricing Policy\u202fv2.4, clause\u202f3.1\u202f(“Pricing Floors”).  \n\n**Additional notes from the policy:**  \n\n- **Relationship‑value adjustment:**\u202fIf the client generates\u202f≥\u202fAED\u202f500\u202fk\u202fp.a. of cross‑sell revenue, the floor may be reduced by up to\u202f25\u202fbps with appropriate credit‑authority approval (clause\u202f2.4).  \n- **Revolving Credit Facilities (RCFs):**\u202fFor an RCF, the BB‑rated drawn‑margin floor is\u202f160\u202fbps over FTP (plus an extra\u202f40\u202fbps for tenors\u202f>\u202f3\u202fyears), plus a\u202f40\u202fbps commitment‑fee floor and a\u202f20\u202fbps facility‑fee floor (clause\u202f3.2).  \n- **Exceptions:**\u202fPricing below these floors requires a formal Pricing Exception (RAROC analysis, commercial justification, and executive approvals) (clause\u202f6.1).'}]}
