2026-06-25 11:25:57,008 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=86feba96ab1f0e27bad1fd521c895d89 span=10e82fb41bac8cb5 parent=- | {'role': 'tool', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call_response', 'id': 'fc_16b9b564-c18b-4dae-aa07-42455367e466', 'response': "Based on FAB's current credit policy, the pricing floors for a **BB-rated corporate term loan** in AED are set as minimum spreads over the internal Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP) rate. The applicable floor depends on the facility tenor:\n\n| Facility Tenor | Minimum Pricing Floor Spread |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **≤ 1 Year** | 165 bps over FTP |\n| **1 – 3 Years** | 210 bps over FTP |\n| **3 – 5 Years** | 260 bps over FTP |\n| **> 5 Years** | 320 bps over FTP |\n\n**Key Application Notes:**\n* **All-In Rate Calculation:** The total minimum all-in rate is `Current FTP Rate + Applicable Floor Spread`. \n* **Pricing Exceptions:** Any loan priced below these standard floors requires a formally documented **Pricing Exception** approved at the appropriate authority level (Segment Credit Head to Group Credit Committee, depending on the deviation).\n* **Relationship Value Adjustment:** A discount of up to 25 bps against the standard floor may be granted if the client demonstrates material cross-sell contributions (revenues > AED 500,000 p.a.), subject to credit authority approval and annual review.\n\n*Citation: [FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · Section 3.1 Corporate Term Loans (Table 3.1) & Section 2.4]*"}]}
2026-06-25 11:25:58,281 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=86feba96ab1f0e27bad1fd521c895d89 span=10e82fb41bac8cb5 parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'text', 'content': '**Pricing Floors for BB‑rated AED Corporate Term Loans**\n\n| Facility Tenor | Minimum Pricing Floor Spread |\n|----------------|------------------------------|\n| ≤\u202f1\u202fYear       | 165\u202fbps over FTP |\n| 1\u202f–\u202f3\u202fYears    | 210\u202fbps over FTP |\n| 3\u202f–\u202f5\u202fYears    | 260\u202fbps over FTP |\n| >\u202f5\u202fYears      | 320\u202fbps over FTP |\n\n**Key Application Notes**\n- **All‑In Rate Calculation:** Total minimum all‑in rate = Current FTP Rate + applicable floor spread.  \n- **Pricing Exceptions:** Loans priced below these floors require a formally documented Pricing Exception approved by the appropriate authority (Segment Credit Head to Group Credit Committee, depending on deviation).  \n- **Relationship Value Adjustment:** Up to 25\u202fbps discount off the standard floor may be granted for clients with material cross‑sell contributions (revenues\u202f>\u202fAED\u202f500,000\u202fp.a.), subject to credit authority approval and annual review.\n\n**Source:** FAB Credit Pricing Policy v2.4, Section\u202f3.1\u202fCorporate Term Loans (Table\u202f3.1) & Section\u202f2.4.'}]}
