2026-06-25 12:12:34,397 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=143e876f9571ce448877abb938da14a6 span=b1f2aa3de59373bb parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call', 'id': 'fc_7049a998-86c7-404e-bf3e-0ad078934cba', 'name': 'query_knowledge_base', 'arguments': '{"question":"pricing floor for BB-rated AED corporate loans"}'}]}
2026-06-25 12:12:34,397 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=143e876f9571ce448877abb938da14a6 span=b1f2aa3de59373bb parent=- | {'role': 'tool', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call_response', 'id': 'fc_7049a998-86c7-404e-bf3e-0ad078934cba', 'response': 'Based on the **FAB Credit Pricing Policy (v2.4)**, the minimum pricing floors for **BB-rated (sub-investment grade) corporate term loans** are set as a minimum credit spread over the applicable Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP) rate. \n\nBecause FTP rates are dynamic and set monthly by Treasury, the absolute floor fluctuates, but the *mandatory spread component* for a BB-rated client is as follows:\n\n| Facility Tenor | Minimum Floor Spread (over FTP) |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **≤ 1 Year** | **165 bps** |\n| **1 – 3 Years** | **210 bps** |\n| **3 – 5 Years** | **260 bps** |\n| **> 5 Years** | **320 bps** |\n\n*Source: [FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 3.1]*\n\n### Key Policy Notes:\n*   **Relationship Value Adjustment:** The required margin may be reduced by up to **25 bps** from the standard floor, but only if the client demonstrates documented cross-sell revenues exceeding AED 500,000 per annum and receives the appropriate credit authority approval. *[Source: FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 2.4]*\n*   **All-In Rate Construction:** The total all-in rate offered to the client cannot fall below the AED FTP rate plus the stated floor spread (e.g., if the AED FTP for the tenor is 5.55%, the minimum all-in rate for a 3-year BB loan is 5.55% + 2.10% = 7.65%).\n*   **Pricing Exceptions:** Any transaction priced below these floors requires a formal Pricing Exception. Minor deviations (up to 15 bps below floor) require Segment Credit Head approval, while larger deviations require Country or Group Credit Committee approval. *[Source: FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 6]*'}]}
2026-06-25 12:12:37,192 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=143e876f9571ce448877abb938da14a6 span=b1f2aa3de59373bb parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'text', 'content': '**Margin analysis for CUST003 (Gulf Star Logistics)**  \n\n| deal_id | deal_date | customer_id | customer_name | customer_segment | region | risk_category | internal_rating | product_id | product_type | currency | tenor | requested_amount | funding_cost_pct | risk_premium_pct | relationship_discount_pct | recommended_price_pct | final_approved_price_pct | expected_margin_pct | deal_outcome | benchmark_rate_pct_treasury | funding_cost_pct_treasury | net_margin_pct | spread_over_benchmark_pct | margin_vs_recommended_pct |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| DEAL024 | 2025-12-15 00:00:00 | CUST003 | Gulf Star Logistics | Corporate | Dubai | Medium | BBB+ | PROD002 | Loan | AED | 60M | 17,600,000 | 6.0 | 0.45 | 0.3 | 8.25 | 8.25 | 1.9 | Won | 5.7 | 6.0 | 1.5 | 2.55 | 0.0 |\n| DEAL026 | 2025-12-22 00:00:00 | CUST003 | Gulf Star Logistics | Corporate | Dubai | Medium | BBB+ | PROD002 | Loan | AED | 60M | 16,200,000 | 6.0 | 0.45 | 0.3 | 8.25 | 8.15 | 1.8 | Won | 5.7 | 6.0 | 1.4 | 2.45 | -0.1 |\n| DEAL038 | 2025-06-04 00:00:00 | CUST003 | Gulf Star Logistics | Corporate | Dubai | Medium | BBB+ | PROD002 | Loan | AED | 24M | 14,000,000 | 5.7 | 0.45 | 0.3 | 7.95 | 7.95 | 1.9 | Won | 5.45 | 5.7 | 1.5 | 2.5 | 0.0 |\n| DEAL059 | 2025-03-10 00:00:00 | CUST003 | Gulf Star Logistics | Corporate | Dubai | Medium | BBB+ | PROD003 | Trade Finance | AED | 3M | 15,700,000 | 5.25 | 0.45 | 0.3 | 6.65 | 6.6 | 1.0 | Won | 5.05 | 5.25 | 0.6 | 1.55 | -0.05 |\n\n*Source: `margin_analysis` view (structured data).*\n\n---\n\n**Pricing floor for BB‑rated AED corporate term loans**  \n\n| Facility Tenor | Minimum Floor Spread (over FTP) |\n|---|---|\n| ≤\u202f1\u202fYear | 165\u202fbps |\n| 1\u202f–\u202f3\u202fYears | 210\u202fbps |\n| 3\u202f–\u202f5\u202fYears | 260\u202fbps |\n| >\u202f5\u202fYears | 320\u202fbps |\n\n*Source: FAB Credit Pricing Policy (v2.4), clause\u202f3.1.*\n\n**Additional policy notes (relevant excerpts):**  \n\n- *Relationship Value Adjustment*: The required margin may be reduced by up to 25\u202fbps if the client generates cross‑sell revenues\u202f>\u202fAED\u202f500,000\u202fp.a. and receives appropriate credit‑authority approval. *Source: FAB Credit Pricing Policy (v2.4), clause\u202f2.4.*  \n- *All‑In Rate Construction*: The all‑in rate cannot fall below **AED\u202fFTP\u202f+\u202ffloor spread** (e.g., AED\u202fFTP\u202f5.55\u202f%\u202f+\u202f260\u202fbps\u202f=\u202f7.65\u202f% for a 3‑year BB loan). *Source: FAB Credit Pricing Policy (v2.4), clause\u202f2.4.*  \n- *Pricing Exceptions*: Deviations below the floor require a formal Pricing Exception; up to 15\u202fbps below needs Segment Credit Head approval; larger deviations need Country or Group Credit Committee approval. *Source: FAB Credit Pricing Policy (v2.4), clause\u202f6.*  '}]}
