 team **within 24\u202fhours of detection**.\n\n**Source passages**  \n\n* FAB Model Risk Management Framework v3.1 – Section\u202f5  \n  ```\n  All model incidents must be reported to the Model Risk Management team within 24 hours of detection, and to the CBUAE within 30 calendar days where the incident is material (threshold: financial impact > AED 1 million or regulatory breach).\n  ```\n\n* CBUAE Circular 2024/BSE/047 – Article\u202f8.2  \n  ```\n  LFIs must notify the Central Bank within 30 calendar days of any AI‑related incident that results in material consumer detriment or regulatory breach.\n  ```\n\n---  \n\n**Verdict**  \n\n- The loan for CUST002 can be priced at **7.3\u202f%** with an expected margin of **1.35\u202f%**, and the customer falls in the **High** profitability tier.  \n- Any material AI model incident must be reported to the CBUAE **within 30\u202fcalendar\u202fdays** (external) and to the internal Model Risk Management team **within 24\u202fhours**.'}]}
