2026-06-25 14:46:55,165 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=94fe18906f589fbde994343c201bfdf8 span=8c15f495e6f1f096 parent=- | {'role': 'tool', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call_response', 'id': 'fc_598738fe-8729-4dff-a22f-64c667a8f804', 'response': 'Based on the **FAB Credit Pricing Policy v2.4**, the minimum pricing floors for a **BB-rated AED Corporate Term Loan** are defined as a risk-based spread over the monthly Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP) rate. \n\nThe specific floor spreads by facility tenor are:\n\n| Facility Tenor | Minimum Pricing Floor Spread |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **≤ 1 Year** | 165 bps |\n| **1 – 3 Years** | 210 bps |\n| **3 – 5 Years** | 260 bps |\n| **> 5 Years** | 320 bps |\n\n**Important Application Notes:**\n* **All-in Rate Calculation:** The total all-in interest rate must not fall below `FTP Rate + Stated Floor Spread`. FTP rates are published monthly by FAB Treasury and vary by currency and tenor bucket.\n* **Relationship Value Adjustments:** In limited cases, a material cross-sell contribution (exceeding AED 500,000 annual revenue) may allow a reduction of up to 25 bps from the standard floor, but this requires documented approval by the relevant credit authority `[FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 2.4]`.\n* **Pricing Exceptions:** Pricing below these floors triggers a mandatory Pricing Exception process. Deviations up to 15 bps below floor require Segment Credit Head approval, while larger deviations require Country or Group Credit Committee approval `[FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 6.2]`.\n\n*Source: [FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · 3.1]*'}]}
2026-06-25 14:46:55,165 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=94fe18906f589fbde994343c201bfdf8 span=8c15f495e6f1f096 parent=- | {'role': 'assistant', 'parts': [{'type': 'text', 'content': '**Pricing floor for BB‑rated AED corporate loans**  \n(Source: query_knowledge_base – *FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4*\u202f·\u202f3.1)\n\n| Facility Tenor | Minimum Pricing Floor Spread |\n|---|---|\n| ≤\u202f1\u202fYear | 165\u202fbps |\n| 1\u202f–\u202f3\u202fYears | 210\u202fbps |\n| 3\u202f–\u202f5\u202fYears | 260\u202fbps |\n| >\u202f5\u202fYears | 320\u202fbps |\n\n**Important Application Notes** – *FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4*\u202f·\u202f2.4  \n- All‑in Rate Calculation: the total all‑in interest rate must not fall below **FTP Rate + Stated Floor Spread**. FTP rates are published monthly by FAB Treasury and vary by currency and tenor bucket.  \n- Relationship Value Adjustments: a material cross‑sell contribution (exceeding AED\u202f500,000 annual revenue) may allow a reduction of up to **25\u202fbps** from the standard floor, but this requires documented approval by the relevant credit authority.  \n- Pricing Exceptions: pricing below these floors triggers a mandatory Pricing Exception process. Deviations up to **15\u202fbps** below floor require Segment Credit Head approval; larger deviations require Country or Group Credit Committee approval. *FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4*\u202f·\u202f6.2  \n\n---\n\n**Margin analysis for CUST003 (Gulf Star Logistics)**  \n(Source: query_structured_data – `margin_analysis`)\n\n| Deal ID | Deal Date | Product | Currency | Tenor | Requested Amount (AED) | Net Margin | Margin vs Recommended | Spread Over Benchmark |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **DEAL024** | 2025‑12‑15 | Loan (PROD002) | AED | 60M | 17,600,000 | 1.50% | 0.00% | 2.55% |\n| **DEAL026** | 2025‑12‑22 | Loan (PROD002) | AED | 60M | 16,200,000 | 1.40% | -0.10% | 2.45% |\n| **DEAL038** | 2025‑06‑04 | Loan (PROD002) | AED | 24M | 14,000,000 | 1.50% | 0.00% | 2.50% |\n| **DEAL059** | 2025‑03‑10 | Trade Finance (PROD003) | AED | 3M | 15,700,000 | 0.60% | -0.05% | 1.55% |\n\n**Detailed Deal Breakdown** (Source: `margin_analysis`)\n\n*DEAL024* – Recommended Price\u202f8.25\u202f% – Final Approved Price\u202f8.25\u202f% – Expected Margin\u202f1.90\u202f% – Funding Cost\u202f6.00\u202f% – Risk Premium\u202f0.45\u202f% – Relationship Discount\u202f0.30\u202f% – Treasury Benchmark\u202f5.70\u202f% – Outcome\u202fWon  \n\n*DEAL026* – Recommended Price\u202f8.25\u202f% – Final Approved Price\u202f8.15\u202f% – Expected Margin\u202f1.80\u202f% – Funding Cost\u202f6.00\u202f% – Risk Premium\u202f0.45\u202f% – Relationship Discount\u202f0.30\u202f% – Treasury Benchmark\u202f5.70\u202f% – Outcome\u202fWon  \n\n*DEAL038* – Recommended Price\u202f7.95\u202f% – Final Approved Price\u202f7.95\u202f% – Expected Margin\u202f1.90\u202f% – Funding Cost\u202f5.70\u202f% – Risk Premium\u202f0.45\u202f% – Relationship Discount\u202f0.30\u202f% – Treasury Benchmark\u202f5.45\u202f% – Outcome\u202fWon  \n\n*DEAL059* – Recommended Price\u202f6.65\u202f% – Final Approved Price\u202f6.60\u202f% – Expected Margin\u202f1.00\u202f% – Funding Cost\u202f5.25\u202f% – Risk Premium\u202f0.45\u202f% – Relationship Discount\u202f0.30\u202f% – Treasury Benchmark\u202f5.05\u202f% – Outcome\u202fWon  '}]}
